.TH HSH 1 "2020-11-26" "Linux" "simple shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- simple shell command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.b ./hsh
[
.I command_string
]
[
.I options
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a command line interpreter created as a project for Holberton School. Hsh is a simplified version of the standard Linux shell. The program was created and compiled on
.I Ubuntu 14.04 LTS
Using
.I GCC 4.8.4.
.SH OPTIONS

.B cd - change directory

.P
.B env - print evironment

.P
.B exit - exit the shell

.SH FILES

.P
.B helper1 - miscellaneous helper functions supporting program

.P
.B Header_shell - header file

.P
.B string_help2 - contains function to parse tokens and other character array manipulation

.P
.B string_help - contains functions to manipulate character arrays

.P
.B prompt - main function to start shell

.P
.B path_parser - contains function to parse the path values of a given environment variable

.SH EXAMPLE
alexnsweet@rocketblaster.com:~/simple_shell$ ./hsh
.P ($)
.P ($)pwd
.P /home/vagrant/simple_shell
.P ($)exit
